<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A9506002002" page = "2">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean inside, outside and around windshield.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove wiper arms. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9406006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove cowl top garnish. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using masking tape, cover body surface around windshield to prevent any damage when cutting the adhesive.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove inner rear view mirror. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9506007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove instrument panel, if necessary. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove head lining, if necessary. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove or cut windshield molding.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Make hole into adhesive with eyeleteer (1) and pass piano string through it.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01950040.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.169mm" ver = "01" gw = "159" gh = "128"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Cut all adhesives of windshield (1) with piano string (2).
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Using the piano string separated from the front windshield glass can damage the body or the instrument panel.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Use the piano string as close to the front windshield glass as possible.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBW101950001.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "48.926mm" ver = "01" gw = "182" gh = "122"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using knife (1), smoothen adhesive remaining (2) on body side (3) and thickness of adhesive should be 1 to 2 mm (0.040 to 0.078 in.).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Before using knife, degrease it with alcohol or the like.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01950042.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "52.482mm" ver = "01" gw = "197" gh = "132"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A9506002003" page = "2">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
If windshield is to be reused, be careful to remove adhesive (1) not to damage primer application surface (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01950043.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "51.593mm" ver = "01" gw = "191" gh = "129"/>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
For proper handling and drying time of primer and adhesive, refer to their maker’s instruction.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<s1>
<ptxt>
 To determine installing position of windshield (1) to body (2), position windshield against body so that clearance between upper end of windshield and body is approximately 4.0 mm (0.16 in.) and clearances between each side end (right &#38; left) of windshield and body are even.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Then put alignment marks (3) on windshield and body.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Windshield clearance
</title>
<ptxt>
“a”: Approx. 4.0 mm (0.16 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A950013.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "62.238mm" ver = "01" gw = "226" gh = "160"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean contact surfaces of old adhesive (4) left on body. Apply primer (2) where paint or bare metal is exposed (3).
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Do not apply primer on adhesive.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8G001950046.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "33.544mm" ver = "01" gw = "164" gh = "79"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.236in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.176in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.236in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "1.176in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
1.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Do not apply primer.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
5.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Body panel
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean area about 30 to 50 mm (1.19 to 1.96 in.) from the edge of windshield with gauze and white gasoline. Dry white gasoline for 10 minutes or more.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply primer onto windshield molding mounting area on windshield (2) and install new windshield molding (3) to windshield.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install new spacers (1) and fasteners (4) to windshield.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A950014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "60.689mm" ver = "01" gw = "147" gh = "156"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply primer to adhesive application area on windshield.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Oil or foreign material adhering to the primer coating can reduce the effectiveness of the adhesive.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Do not allow oil or foreign material to adhere to the primer coating.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply adhesive (1) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
If more than 5 minutes elapse after applying adhesive to the front windshield glass (2), the adhesive can harden, preventing the front windshield glass from being attached firmly.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Attach the front windshield glass to the body within 5 minutes of applying adhesive.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Use rubber sucker grip to carry glass after adhesive is applied.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<spec>
<title>
Adhesive amount and application area on windshield
</title>
<ptxt>
Width of adhesive “a”: Approx. 7.0 mm (0.28 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Height of adhesive “b”: Approx. 15.0 mm (0.59 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Application area “c”: Approx. 11.5 mm (0.45 in.), “d”: Approx. 25.0 mm (0.98 in.), “e”: Approx. 13.4 mm (0.53 in.), “f”: Approx. 34.0 mm (1.34 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A950016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "111.086mm" ver = "01" gw = "225" gh = "298"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "4" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.236in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "1.732in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "0.236in"/>
<colspec colnum = "4" colname = "4" colwidth = "0.748in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
3.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Windshield molding
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" valign = "top" align = "right">
<ptxt>
4.
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "4" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" valign = "top" align = "left">
<ptxt>
Spacer
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Holding windshield (3) with rubber sucker grips (1), align fasteners (2) with holes (4) of body, align alignment marks put in Step 1) and install windshield.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A950017.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "82.149mm" ver = "01" gw = "223" gh = "216"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Dry adhesive.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
If the following precautions are not taken when drying the adhesive, the front windshield glass may slip, preventing it from being attached firmly.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Take the following precautions when drying adhesive.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Avoid quickly closing a door before complete hardening of the adhesive. Closing a door quickly could cause the windshield to become loose or even come off. If a door must be closed before the adhesive hardens completely, open all side windows first and then gently close the door.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
If molding is not securely in place, hold it down with tape until the adhesive completely hardens.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Refrain from driving until the adhesive completely hardens.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not use infrared light or like for drying.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention4>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check for water leakage 1 or 2 hours after installing windshield. If leakage is found, remove and install windshield again.
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
If the following precautions are not taken when checking for water leakage, the windshield glass may not attach properly.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Take the following precautions when checking for water leakage.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not apply excessive water pressure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I2RH01950051.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.958mm" ver = "01" gw = "195" gh = "127"/>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not blow compressed air directly at adhesive applied part when drying.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention4>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install head lining if it has been removed. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install instrument panel if it has been removed. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install inner rear view mirror. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9506007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install cowl top garnish. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9806005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install wiper arms. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9406006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
